/-!
# Witness-chain kernel checker — the fused Bool fold and the `A = 19` assault

`Step00ExtremalGapGeometry` proved the wall instance `A = 17` by `decide` on the Prop-level
`WitnessChain` and recorded the `A = 19` postmortem: the Prop route blew a 16 GB memory budget
(`P = 1616615`, 33412 witnesses).  This file replaces the Prop decision procedure by a fused
Bool-valued single-pass fold:

* `cleanListB qs m` — one `Bool` pass over the finite clock list `qs` (two `%` per clock);
* `chainB` / `witnessChainB` — ONE tail-position fold checking, per witness, the four facts
  (strict increase, gap `≤ L`, bound `≤ P`, cleanliness) and the wrap inequality at the end —
  no `Finset`, no `Decidable` instances, no per-conjunct re-traversal;
* `cleanListB_correct`, `clean_of_cleanListB`, `chainB_spec`, `witnessChainB_correct` — the
  one-directional soundness chain from the Bool fold back to the Prop `WitnessChain` (only
  this direction is needed: the fold is a certificate CHECKER, not a decision procedure);
* `witnessChainB_17` — the calibration gate (`decide +kernel` on the 2193-witness chain);
* `witnessChainB_19` / `witnessChain_19` / `cleanGapBound_19` / `twinJacobsthal_at_19` — the
  new scale.  HONESTY CORRECTION: `51 = ⌊19²/7⌋` is the greedy chain STEP, not the gap —
  the true gap is `G(19) = 25` (ledger L30, ratio ≈ 0.49); an earlier version wrongly
  claimed "G(19) = 51 EXACT/tight".  (Curiosity: `⌊19²/14⌋ = 25` IS genuinely tight —
  the two-regime observation, see the Sharp wall.);
* `twin_gap_below_wall` — the cheap general bridge: below the `A²` sieve horizon every
  window `(k, k+L]` served by a `CleanGapBound` contains an actual TWIN center
  (`sink_is_twin`), with concrete instances at `A ∈ {13, 17}`.
-/

